OL,3,CFootball community pays tribute player
OL,4,Cwho died after battling cancer
OL,6,FThe footballing community have paid
OL,7,Ftribute to a 20-year-old footballer
OL,8,Ffrom Dumfries and Galloway who has
OL,9,Fdied after a battle with cancer.
OL,11,FCharlie Watson, from Lochmaben, was
OL,12,Fdiagnosed with stage four skin cancer
OL,13,Fin 2023 but continued to play the
OL,14,Fsport he loved while undergoing
OL,15,Fchemotherapy.
OL,17,FHe played for Queen of the South and
OL,18,FDalbeattie Star before signing for
OL,19,FThreave Rovers in 2024. They have
OL,20,Fdescribed Charlie as an "absolute
OL,21,Fwarrior" who was a "true inspiration."
